President Biden has declared a major disaster in Texas due to a severe winter storm that occurred from January 30 to February 2, 2023. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The counties of Bastrop, Blanco, Burleson, Burnet, Hays, Henderson, Kendall, Lee, Leon, Milam, Robertson, Travis, and Williamson are eligible for federal funding for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Hazard mitigation measures statewide will also receive federal funding. Gerard M. Stolar of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.